{
  "texts": [
    "Unless explicitly stated, we train on 10% of training sets to mimic a real-world setting where the number of human ratings is relatively small: from hundreds (Offset Bias) to thousands (Nectar).",
    "All results are averaged over 10 random training sets to avoid bias to a given split.",
    "Beyond the base judges, we consider three baselines.",
    "The first baseline is a supervised fine-tuned base judge to human scores from prompts instantiated with evaluated responses.",
    "We call it SFT."
  ]
}